Class I18NManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.lambeck.pned.i18n.I18NManager

  • public class I18NManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This "internationalized" ("i18n") Strings manager provides localized messages and names.
    Author:
    Thomas Lambeck, 4128320

      • getMessage

        public java.lang.String getMessage(java.lang.String key)
        Calls getString() with the resource bundle for messages and forwards the result.

        Note: In opposition to (button) names is an "&" within a message not a "mnemonic marker" but just a part of the text.
        Parameters:
        key - The given key
        Returns:
        The string for the given key

      • getMnemonicName

        public MnemonicString getMnemonicName(java.lang.String key)
        Calls getMnemonicString() with the resource bundle for names (buttons names etc.) and forwards the result.

        Note: (button) names can contain an "&" as "mnemonic marker".
        Parameters:
        key - The given key
        Returns:
        A MnemonicString object with two values: The string for the given key and the mnemonic

      • getNameOnly

        public java.lang.String getNameOnly(java.lang.String key)
        Calls getMnemonicString() with the resource bundle for names (buttons names etc.) and forwards only the name.

        Note: Using getMnemonicString() removes the "mnemonic marker" from the name. Example "&File" => "File"
        Parameters:
        key - The given key
        Returns:
        The string for the given key without the mnemonic mark

      • getMnemonicString

        private MnemonicString getMnemonicString(java.lang.String key,
                                         java.util.ResourceBundle bundle)
        Gets the string and the mnemonic (after the char "&") for the given key from the specified resource bundle.

        Note: The mnemonic is a String (like "A"), not a KeyEvent (like KeyEvent.VK_A). Convert the mnemonic into an int for use in a setMnemonic() method!
        Parameters:
        key - The given key
        bundle - The specified resource bundle
        Returns:
        A MnemonicString object with two values: The string for the given key and the mnemonic
